description: Best practices for Angular applications
globs: **/*.{ts}
---

- Use Angular's dependency injection system for better modularity and testability
- Implement OnPush change detection strategy for performance optimization
- Utilize reactive forms for complex form handling and validation
- Leverage Angular's built-in pipes for data transformation and internationalization
- Use NgRx or similar state management for large-scale applications to manage global state
- Implement lazy loading of modules to improve initial load time
- Use Angular's HttpClient for making HTTP requests and handling responses
- Implement proper error handling using RxJS operators and Angular's error handling mechanisms
